content_sections.content:
Learn how to create a pill navigation menu with CSS.
Pill Navigation
Home
News
Contact
About

Create a Pill Navigation
Step 1) Add HTML:
Example
<div class="pill-nav">
<a class="active" href="#home">Home</a>
<a href="#news">News</a>
<a href="#contact">Contact</a>
<a href="#about">About</a>
</div>
Step 2) Add CSS:
Example
/* Style the links inside the pill navigation menu */
.pill-nav a {
display: inline-block;
color: black;
text-align: center;
padding: 14px;
text-decoration: none;
font-size: 17px;
border-radius: 5px;
}
/* Change the color of links on mouse-over */
.pill-nav a:hover {
background-color: #ddd;
color: black;
}
/* Add a color to the active/current link */
.pill-nav a.active {
background-color: dodgerblue;
color: 
  white;
}

Vertical Pill Navigation
Add
display: block
to the links, and they will appear vertically instead of horizontally:
Example
Home
News
Contact
About

Tip:
See also
How To Create a Top Navigation Menu
.
Tip:
Go to our
CSS Navbar Tutorial
to learn more about navigation bars.

